# Other
# artifacts/ is operator-local only — manual-test scan fixtures,
# export drops, debug dumps.  Not committed: the fixtures can carry
# environment-specific scan data and the operator owns them per host.
# The parametrized dispatcher test (test_artifacts_manual_dispatcher.py)
# skips itself when artifacts/manual/ is absent, so CI on a fresh
# checkout stays green without the fixtures present.
artifacts/
CLAUDE.md
notes.txt
troubleshooting_*

# Internal docs kept local-only — not published to the public repo.
# CLAUDE.md (architecture/ops guidance) and CHANGELOG.md (detailed dev
# history) reveal internals with no runtime purpose.  AGENTS.md is NOT
# here: the backend serves it at /agents-guide, so it must stay tracked.
CHANGELOG.md

# Session scratch / shared debug bundles — operator-local, never committed.
# Design-discussion notes, ad-hoc patches, and copied-over container log
# dumps from the remote host.
*.patch
dashboard_changes.txt
*_changes.txt
all_container_logs.txt
*_container_logs.txt

# Backend startup resolves AGENTS.md / platform_version.json relative to
# its CWD; running it with a CWD lacking the real (repo-root) copies — e.g.
# the mounted test container — leaves 0-byte stand-ins here. Never real.
/backend/AGENTS.md
/backend/platform_version.json

# Docker bind-mount placeholder — created at 0 bytes by the SBOM mount
# in docker-compose.yml when test runs that also bind ./backend to /app.
# Never the real file (real one lives at frontend/package-lock.json).
/backend/frontend-package-lock.json

# Oneoff planning docs
suggestions.md

# deploy.sh rollback snapshot state (B2-1) — operator-local, per-deploy
.deploy-rollback-state
